sls christian fellowship stanford law school stanford law school search utility navigation test directory news center library events publications contact & maps information for prospective students alumni employers current students faculty & staff the experience student life student organizations sls christian fellowship main navigation the experience student life scholarly life areas of interest beyond campus careers exec ed alumni life the school campus people offices & administration facts history giving the program degrees courses clinics programs & centers tuition & financial aid close sls christian fellowship overview sls christian fellowship is a national organization of lawyers judges law professors and law students stanford's chapter is a nondenominational group of students and others in the law school community who meet weekly to study the bible and to encourage one another to integrate faith in jesus christ with the study and practice of law sls christian fellowship seeks to foster discussion of religious issues to assert a high standard of legal ethics and to promote religious freedom the society brings christian attorneys teachers and judges to campus to address new issues concerning religion and society for more information contact allie leeper co president aren balabanian co president kevin o herin co president janiece jenkins co president recorded & past events november 2008 work life balance november 13 2008 from 12 45 pm 2 00 pm february 2008 cls meeting february 20 2008 from 4 15 pm 5 15 pm cls meeting february 13 2008 from 4 15 pm 5 15 pm october 2007 christian law students meeting october 23 2007 from 3 25 pm 4 30 pm march 2007 cls dinner with cristina arguedas march 20 2007 from 6 00 pm 8 00 pm contact information stanford law school sls christian fellowship blocksom stanford edu rgyoung stanford edu cloudy 57 f 2012 stanford university system requirements help virtual tour
